{
  "id": "medium_05_ts",
  "title": "Inventory Analyzer (TS)",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "category": "Generator exhaustion + unimplemented function",
  "description": "Given a list of inventory items, each with `\"name\"` (str), `\"value\"` (int), and `\"active\"` (bool), return a dict with:\n- `\"active_names\"` — names of active items in input order.\n- `\"stats\"` — `{\"count\", \"total\", \"average\"}` computed over active item values. Return all zeros if no active items exist.\n\n**Example 1:**\nInput:\n```\n[\n  {\"name\": \"widget\",    \"value\": 100, \"active\": true},\n  {\"name\": \"gadget\",    \"value\": 50,  \"active\": false},\n  {\"name\": \"doohickey\", \"value\": 75,  \"active\": true}\n]\n```\nOutput: `{\"active_names\": [\"widget\", \"doohickey\"], \"stats\": {\"count\": 2, \"total\": 175, \"average\": 87.5}}`\n\n**Example 2:**\nInput: `[{\"name\": \"x\", \"value\": 5, \"active\": false}]`\nOutput: `{\"active_names\": [], \"stats\": {\"count\": 0, \"total\": 0, \"average\": 0}}`\n\n**Constraints:**\n- `1 <= len(items) <= 200`\n- `1 <= value <= 100000`\n\n**Tasks:** `active_names` always returns empty — trace how `filterActive` returns its result and how many times it gets iterated. Also implement `summarize(values)` in `processor.js`.",
  "files": [
    {
      "name": "processor.ts",
      "editable": true
    },
    {
      "name": "main.ts",
      "editable": true
    }
  ],
  "entry_module": "main",
  "entry_function": "analyzeInventory",
  "test_cases": [
